<TITLE> India says not considering banning BlackBerry </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 New Delhi, Mar 15 (Reuters) - India is not considering banning Research In Motion's BlackBerry services at this point of time, the top official in the telecom ministry said on Friday. "There is no question of banning at this point," telecom secretary Siddhartha Behura told reporters, adding the government was talking to telecom operators and RIM to resolve its security concern
